Package com.newatlanta.commons.vfs.provider.gae

Class Summary
GaeFileName Supports serialization required by memcache (see GaeMemcacheFilesCache).
GaeFileNameParser Parses GAE URIs and creates GaeFileName instances.
GaeFileObject Stores metadata for "files" and "folders" within GaeVFS and manages interactions with the Google App Engine datastore.
GaeFileProvider Configures the GaeFileNameParser and creates GaeFileSystem instances.
GaeFileSystem Creates GaeFileObject instances.
GaeFileSystemManager Implements the Combined Local option for GaeVFS.
GaeRandomAccessContent The class mimics java.io.RandomAccessFile, which has this description: "Instances of this class support both reading and writing to a random access file.
GaeVFS This class is the entry point for interacting with the Google App Engine Virtual File System (GaeVFS).
GaeVfsServlet GaeVfsServlet uploads files into the GAE virtual file system (GaeVFS) and then serves them out again.
